wliNicTable.name: wliNicTable
wliNicTable.description: Network Interface Card information for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliNicEntry.name: wliNicEntry
wliNicEntry.description: Network Interface Card information for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliNicIndex.name: wliNicIndex
wliNicIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this NIC information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wliNicBusType.name: wliNicBusType
wliNicBusType.description: The bus-type supported by this NIC.

wliNicSlot.name: wliNicSlot
wliNicSlot.description: The I/O Base Address (ISA/AT) or Slot Number (MC) or Socket Number (PCMCIA) used by this NIC. For ISA/AT (and alike) Base Addresses, the following values are used: 1='0300'H, 2='0390'H, 3='03C0'H, 4='03E0'H

wliNicIrq.name: wliNicIrq
wliNicIrq.description: The Interrupt Request Number (IRQ) used by this NIC.

wliNicError.name: wliNicError
wliNicError.description: A counter for miscellaneous board errors. It indicates (intermittent) NIC hardware problems.

wliNicOutOfRxResource.name: wliNicOutOfRxResource
wliNicOutOfRxResource.description: A counter for the number of times the NIC is out of resources for the receiver, causing the receiver to be switched off temporarily.

wliPhyTable.name: wliPhyTable
wliPhyTable.description: PHY status information and control variables for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliPhyEntry.name: wliPhyEntry
wliPhyEntry.description: PHY status information and control variables for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliPhyIndex.name: wliPhyIndex
wliPhyIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this PHY information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wliPhyDsp.name: wliPhyDsp
wliPhyDsp.description: The Digital Signal Processor on the board.

wliPhyFrequency.name: wliPhyFrequency
wliPhyFrequency.description: The mid-point of the frequency band this WaveLAN NIC operates in.

wliPhyNwid.name: wliPhyNwid
wliPhyNwid.description: The WaveLAN Network ID (NWID) this RF-modem is currently configured for.

wliPhyRfSilenceLevel.name: wliPhyRfSilenceLevel
wliPhyRfSilenceLevel.description: The RF Silence Level as currently read from the RF modem.

wliPhyOwnNwid.name: wliPhyOwnNwid
wliPhyOwnNwid.description: Own NWID counter; the number of frames received with the configured NWID.

wliPhyOtherNwid.name: wliPhyOtherNwid
wliPhyOtherNwid.description: Other NWID counter; the number of frames received with different NWID than configured.

wliPhyLowSnr.name: wliPhyLowSnr
wliPhyLowSnr.description: The number of times the Signal to Noise Ratio (sample) of a frame reception was low.

wliPhyGoodSnr.name: wliPhyGoodSnr
wliPhyGoodSnr.description: The number of times the Signal to Noise Ratio (sample) of a frame reception was good.

wliPhyExcellentSnr.name: wliPhyExcellentSnr
wliPhyExcellentSnr.description: The number of times the Signal to Noise Ratio (sample) of a frame reception was excellent.

wliMacTable.name: wliMacTable
wliMacTable.description: MAC status information and control variables for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliMacEntry.name: wliMacEntry
wliMacEntry.description: MAC status information and control variables for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliMacIndex.name: wliMacIndex
wliMacIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this MAC information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wliMacDeferredTransmissions.name: wliMacDeferredTransmissions
wliMacDeferredTransmissions.description: A counter for the number of frames for which the transmission attempt is delayed because the medium is busy. (same as dot3StatsDeferredTransmissions)

wliMacFCSErrors.name: wliMacFCSErrors
wliMacFCSErrors.description: A counter for the number of frames received that do not pass the FCS check and/or that are not an integral number of octets in length. WaveLAN hardware does not distinguish between FCS errors and Alignment errors. (same as dot3StatsFCSErrors + dot3StatsAlignmentErrors)

wliMacFrameTooLongs.name: wliMacFrameTooLongs
wliMacFrameTooLongs.description: A counter for the number of frames received that exceed the maximum permitted frame size for the medium (1518 bytes). (same as dot3StatsFrameTooLongs)

wliMacFrameTooShorts.name: wliMacFrameTooShorts
wliMacFrameTooShorts.description: A counter for the number of frames received that are shorter than the minimum permitted frame size for the medium (64 bytes)

wliMacDeferLimits.name: wliMacDeferLimits
wliMacDeferLimits.description: The number of times a frame is not transmitted because the CSMA/CA defer limit is reached

wliDriverTable.name: wliDriverTable
wliDriverTable.description: Driver information for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliDriverEntry.name: wliDriverEntry
wliDriverEntry.description: Driver information for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliDriverIndex.name: wliDriverIndex
wliDriverIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this driver information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wliDriverName.name: wliDriverName
wliDriverName.description: The name of the software driver for this WaveLAN network interface.

wliDriverVersion.name: wliDriverVersion
wliDriverVersion.description: The version number of the software driver. A text string as 'mm.nn.pp', where mm = major release number nn = point release number pp = optional patch number

wliEncTable.name: wliEncTable
wliEncTable.description: Encryption status information and control variables for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliEncEntry.name: wliEncEntry
wliEncEntry.description: Encryption status information and control variables for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliEncIndex.name: wliEncIndex
wliEncIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this encryption information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wliEncSelect.name: wliEncSelect
wliEncSelect.description: Whether encryption is enabled or disabled.

wliMcastDelayTable.name: wliMcastDelayTable
wliMcastDelayTable.description: Information about the Multicast Delay feature for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wliMcastDelayEntry.name: wliMcastDelayEntry
wliMcastDelayEntry.description: Information about the Multicast Delay feature for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wliMcastDelayIndex.name: wliMcastDelayIndex
wliMcastDelayIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this Multicast Delay information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of wliIndex (and ifIndex).

wliMcastNumberOfAps.name: wliMcastNumberOfAps
wliMcastNumberOfAps.description: The total number of Access Points in the coverage area. Together with wliMcastApSequenceNumber this is used to determine the delays before and after the transmission of each multicast frame. This results in a transmission slot per Access Point per multicast frame. 0 means: no multicast delay specified (use default mechanism).

wliMcastApSequenceNumber.name: wliMcastApSequenceNumber
wliMcastApSequenceNumber.description: The sequence number of this Access Point in the coverage area. Together with wliMcastNumberOfAps this is used to determine the delays before and after the transmission of each multicast frame. This results in a transmission slot per Access Point per multicast frame.

wliMcastRepeatCount.name: wliMcastRepeatCount
wliMcastRepeatCount.description: The number of times a multicast frame transmission is to be repeated.
